<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I use <code>set-fontset-font</code> to set the fonts for my language, and I noticed that only latin fonts will be affected by <code>text-scale-adjust</code> while the asian fonts remain the same size.</p> <p>But the scaling does work when using emacs without a config file (<code>emacs -Q</code>) or when I didn&#39;t specify the fonts via <code>set-fontset-font</code>.</p> <p><a href="https://github.com/funk443/dotfiles/blob/master/.emacs.d/config.org">My emacs config file can be found here.</a></p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p><a href="http://baohaojun.github.io/perfect-emacs-chinese-font.html">Check this site for solution.</a></p> <p><a href="https://preview.redd.it/7m7oaxutlkc91.png?width=272&amp;format=png&amp;auto=webp&amp;s=29a50432b68971ad0fd2a581659b5ef5410e3509">With my config.</a></p> <p><a href="https://preview.redd.it/bmlwh1llmkc91.png?width=413&amp;format=png&amp;auto=webp&amp;s=e8fb24d4fecdde493b3e80185465d4d2e0e918b6">Without a config file.</a></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/funk443"> /u/funk443 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w30a54/font_size_doesnt_change_while_using/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w30a54/font_size_doesnt_change_while_using/">[comments]</a></span>